        "Upstream URL": "https://github.com/tencent/tquic",
        "Description": "tquic is a high-performance, lightweight QUIC protocol implementation written in Rust, developed by Tencent. It fully complies with the IETF QUIC standard (RFC 9000/RFC 9001/RFC 9002) and is optimized for low-latency, high-throughput network communication scenarios. It supports multiple transport layer features such as connection migration, 0-RTT handshake, and stream multiplexing, and is suitable for both server-side and embedded device-side QUIC protocol stack integration."
    }
]